BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:Dlq99tZNzpbFy0S6ImYlV
SUMMARY:Op-Eds for Academics | IN-PERSON Workshop
DTSTAMP:20260301T153239Z
DTSTART:20260303T220000Z
DESCRIPTION:Event interval: Single day event\n\nCampus room: 115 ABC\n\nAcc
	essibility Contact: mmjones@uw.edu\n\nEvent Types: Workshops\n\nEvent spon
	sors: Society \\+ Technology at UW\, Center for an Informed Public\n\nTarg
	et Audience: Society \\+ Technology at UW and CIP community of researchers
	 interested in translating their work\n\nLink: https://tinyurl.com/inperso
	n-opedsforacademics-uw\n\nOp-eds for Academics \\(In-PERSON\\) is a hands-
	on workshop hosted by Society \\+ Technology at UW and the Center for an I
	nformed Public designed to help you translate your research into compellin
	g public commentary. Academic research is deeply relevant to pressing issu
	es of our times\, but it can be challenging to know how to reach audiences
	 beyond the academy.\n\nThis work shop helps you build practical skills fo
	r bringing your expertise to a wider audience by focusing on the ins and o
	uts of op-ed writing. We'll kick off with a brief panel discussion from me
	mbers of the UW commu nity who have written op-eds\, then we'll discuss ho
	w you can do the same -- from identifying a timely hook\, crafting a persu
	asive short piece\, and navigating the submissions process. Come prepared 
	to hear from colleagues\, use resources\, and participate in interactive e
	xercise s. The ambitious may leave with a draft op-ed and a concrete plan 
	for submitting it. Everyone will gain a clearer understanding about how to
	 write for new audiences.\n\nREGISTER:\n\ntinyurl.com…\n\nCo-hosts and fac
	ilitators: Monika Sengul-Jones \\(Society \\+ Technology at UW\\) and Ali 
	Durran \\(Center for an Informed Public\\) University of Washington\, Seat
	tle\n\nEmail with questions and/or to request specific accommodations.\n\n
	mmjones@uw.edu\n\nor\n\nadurran@uw.edu\n\nCan't make this event? We're off
	ering this workshop ONLINE on Thursday\, March 5\, 2026 from 2 PM - 4 PM.\
	n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/op-eds-for-academics-in-p
	erson-workshop/18084615/2026-03-03T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/op-eds-for-academics-in-p
	erson-workshop/18084615/2026-03-03T00
LOCATION:University of Washington\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
