BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:lrWpz4pBwBtmwDlgswvw5
SUMMARY:City Council Regular Hybrid Meeting
DTSTAMP:20260301T153239Z
DTSTART:20260304T010000Z
DESCRIPTION:January 29\, 20206 - Notice is hereby given that the Mercer Isl
	and City Council will hold a public hearing at its Hybrid Meeting on Tuesd
	 ay\, March 3\, 2026\, at approximately 5pm\, to receive comments on Ordin
	a nce No. 26-02\, renewing interim regulations in MICC 19.16.010 related t
	o emergency shelters and housing\, transitional housing\, and permanent su
	pportive housing in response to E2SHB 1220.\n\nThe public hearing will b e
	 held in person and using Zoom. The public will have the opportunity to c 
	omment during the public hearing by either attending in person\, calling i
	n\, or logging onto the meeting via Zoom. Written comments may be submitte
	d to the City of Mercer Island by e-mail to council@mercerisland.gov until
	  such time that the public hearing is adjourned.\n\nDetailed instruction 
	s on how to comment live during the public hearing will be available onlin
	 e on or before February 25\, 2026\, at: https://www.mercerisland.gov/city
	council.\n\nAndrea Larson\, CMC\n\nCity Clerk\n\nNotice:\n\nCity Council C
	alendar - January 29\, 2026\n\nCity Council Agenda Distribution List - Jan
	uary 29\,  2026\n\nWebsite Public Notice - January 29\, 2026\n\nMercer Isl
	and Reporter - January 28\, 2026\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/
	details/city-council-regular-hybrid-meeting/18066423/2026-03-03T00\n\nFrom
	 SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/city-council-regular-hybr
	id-meeting/18066423/2026-03-03T00
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:PnppkMQUyu_-IeAzNyMl5
SUMMARY:Baking Fundamentals: Cookies\, Cakes\, Custards and More
DTSTAMP:20260301T153239Z
DTSTART:20260304T010000Z
DESCRIPTION:Would you like to be able to make a variety of beautiful and de
	licious baked treats with confidence? Gain fundamental skills and knowledg
	e for baking in this hands-on class.\n\nWe will learn about ingredients\, 
	interactions\, and techniques\, using a variety of mixing methods\, recipe
	s\, and best practices. And we will make a broad range of yummy foods\, su
	ch as muffins\, biscuits\, sponges\, chiffons\, angel food cakes\, quiche\
	, pâte à choux\, custards\, crèmes\, pastry doughs\, pies\, tarts\, layer 
	cakes\, frostings\, meringue\, buttercreams\, and specialty desserts.\n\nE
	njoy making delectable baked goods\, both sweet and savory. We will also d
	iscuss alternative ingredients for people with restrictive diets\, food se
	nsitivities\, and food allergies.\n\nTake advantage of the large\, well-eq
	uipped kitchen at Seattle Central's Culinary Academy. Learn some of the mo
	st useful tips from an experienced chef\, and develop practices for workin
	g in a clean\, safe\, and efficient way.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/e
	vents/#/details/baking-fundamentals-cookies-cakes-custards-and-more/177552
	04/2026-03-03T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/baking-fundamentals-cooki
	es-cakes-custards-and-more/17755204/2026-03-03T00
LOCATION:Seattle Central College Continuing Education\, 1701 Broadway\, Sea
	ttle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
