BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:cG9D05uFdyJh0VSlwxBMB
SUMMARY:Nonviolence Training: Can the University be a "House of Peace"?
DTSTAMP:20260301T153239Z
DTSTART:20260304T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Training with Faculty\, Staff\, and Community: Can the Universi
	ty be a “House of Peace”?\n\nWednesday\, March 4\, 9am-12pm\, with breakfa
	st at 8:30am\n\nOberto Commons\, Sinegal 200\n\n \n\nPope Leo has called o
	n every community across the globe to become a “house of peace.” This work
	shop will use nonviolent tools and exercises to explore what this metaphor
	 could mean in practical terms to Seattle University. Is it already a “hou
	se of peace”? How might it become more of a “house of peace”?\n\n \n\nKen 
	Butigan is a changemaker who has organized campaigns and movements resisti
	ng war\, challenging nuclear weapons\, and standing with the unhoused. He 
	was a founder of the Pledge of Resistance\, which mobilized nonviolent dir
	ect action for a decade to end US military intervention in Central America
	. He works with Pace e Bene’s Campaign Nonviolence that mobilizes thousand
	s of actions in the U.S. and around the world every year challenging war\,
	 poverty\, racism\, and environmental destruction. He is a senior advisor 
	to Pax Christi International’s Catholic Institute for Nonviolence based in
	 Rome. He taught for many years in the Peace\, Justice\, and Conflict Stud
	ies Program at DePaul University in Chicago. He hails originally from Seat
	tle.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/nonviolence-training
	-can-the-university-be-a-house-of-peace/17882132/2026-03-04T00\n\nFrom SEA
	today - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/nonviolence-training-can-
	the-university-be-a-house-of-peace/17882132/2026-03-04T00
LOCATION:Northwest Worklofts (Commons)\, 107 West Denny Way\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:1mIUZiC88um2Z-itYwgy0
SUMMARY:2026 Winter Community Resource Fair
DTSTAMP:20260301T153239Z
DTSTART:20260304T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Organization: Workforce Development Organizer: Sheila.Walton@lw
	tech.edu Event Locator: 2025-AAFTWD\n\nJoin us for the LWTech 2026 Winter 
	Community Resource Fair\n\nWednesday March 4th\, 2026\, 10a.m. - 1p.m. in 
	the main E ast Mall area!\n\nRepresentatives from local community organiza
	tions will be available to assist people in navigating and accessing suppo
	rt for basic needs\, employment\, education\, and much more. T his is a fr
	ee public event that is open to LWTech students and community members and 
	parking is always FREE! A variety of college and community resources will 
	be represented.\n\nGet information to these resources:\n\nTraining and Edu
	cation\n\nHousing\n\nTransportation\n\nFood\n\nMental Health\n\nHealthcare
	\n\nDepartment of Social and Health Services \\(DSHS\\)\n\nEmployment Reso
	urces\n\nAnd much more!\n\nAttendees can register to attend at:\n\nhttps:/
	/seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/2026-winter-community-resource-fair
	/17679611/2026-03-04T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/2026-winter-community-res
	ource-fair/17679611/2026-03-04T00
LOCATION:East Building Mall E180 - All Spaces\, Kirkland\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT4H30M
END:VEVENT
