BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:7_JkynkZ8FaMZ29eUWlXt
SUMMARY:RISE: A Summit on Student Success
DTSTAMP:20260301T153239Z
DTSTART:20260305T160000Z
DESCRIPTION:RISE: A Summit for Student Success\n\nResilience\, Innovation\,
	 and Student Engagement\n\n \n\nBased on last year's overwhelming success\
	, we will be holding the RISE Summit for a second year and intend to make 
	this an annual event. This university-wide event brings together faculty\,
	 staff\, and leadership to collaborate on innovative strategies that advan
	ce student success and engagement.\n\n \n\nIn addition to high-impact prac
	tices in student success and engagement\, this year\, we’ll also have a pa
	rticular focus on AI\, an emerging technology that is impacting higher edu
	cation. There will be a plenary session and several breakout sessions addr
	essing the topic: What does teaching\, learning\, and assessment look like
	 in the age of Artificial Intelligence?\n\n \n\nWe encourage you to attend
	 all or part of this day. The Summit is an opportunity to share insights\,
	 spark ideas\, and help shape initiatives that will guide the student expe
	rience at Seattle University. Specifically\, the focus on pedagogy and AI 
	is critically important for our faculty at this time. \n\n \n\nA detailed 
	agenda and additional information are forthcoming.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6am
	city.com/events/#/details/rise-a-summit-on-student-success/17217840/2026-0
	3-05T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/rise-a-summit-on-student-
	success/17217840/2026-03-05T00
LOCATION:Student Center\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT8H
END:VEVENT
