UID:P04F-OjpHz00tL8uiCDzC
SUMMARY:Womxn & Blues: Be What You Want To Be
DTSTAMP:20260301T153240Z
DTSTART:20260312T143000Z
DESCRIPTION:Doors 6:30\, Show 7:30. Tickets: $20 advance\, $25 door Featuri
	ng: Amber Flame\, Carly T\, Havilah Rand & Najah Todd The Blues have long 
	been a rally cry transforming personal and collective hardships – stemming
	 from racial injustice and systemic oppression – into a musical language o
	f resistance and essential expression. Rooted in field hollers and call-an
	d-response\, these songs provided emotional resilience and solidarity with
	in Black communities. Continue the journey with us as we explore historic 
	and current ideations of this truly American art form. In the song\, Be Wh
	at You Want To Be\, Koko Taylor lays out both the invitation and consequen
	ce in living by this declaration. This session’s artists have their own ta
	ke on the theme.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/womxn-bl
	ues-be-what-you-want-to-be/18252363/2026-03-12T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All E
	vents
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/womxn-blues-be-what-you-w
	ant-to-be/18252363/2026-03-12T00
LOCATION:The Royal Room\, 5000 Rainier Ave South\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
