UID:f0F1U4ewIS5VF5CMFUZNh
SUMMARY:Storytime with Southeast Youth & Family Services
DTSTAMP:20260301T153240Z
DTSTART:20260314T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a monthly storytime with Southeast Youth & Family S
	ervices! We're proud to partner with our friends at Southeast Youth & Fami
	ly Services. Each month\, one of their Early Learning Specialists will rea
	d aloud to kids in our events space\, followed by a craft activity. Books 
	may be read in English\, Spanish\, Somali and/or Amharic depending on the 
	needs of the audience. Stories will be geared toward younger kids\, but al
	l are welcome.  For over 50 years\, Southeast Youth and Family Services ha
	s dedicated itself to serving children and youth in south Seattle and grea
	ter King County. Since its founding\, this Black-led organization has uphe
	ld the core value of community—embracing the belief that it takes a villag
	e to support and nurture families. Together\, we raise the next generation
	.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/storytime-with-southeas
	t-youth-family-services/18167385/2026-03-14T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Even
	ts
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/storytime-with-southeast-
	youth-family-services/18167385/2026-03-14T00
LOCATION:Third Place Books Seward Park\, 5041 Wilson Ave S\, Seattle\, WA
